We, the Board, are very excited to welcome our students back to school as we remain Committed to Excellence.
Sincerely- The Ocean CIty Board of Education

ADMISSIONS.YALE.EDU
Yale Educator Award Winners | Yale College Undergraduate Admissions

Ocean City High School
September 2 at 6:54 PM ·

Congratulations to our very own, Mrs. Mary McDowell-Campo, for being chosen by Yale University as one of their recipients of the 2020 Yale Educator Award! 🏆

Mrs. McDowell-Campo was one of 24 counselors chosen for the award from across 41 states and 19 countries. She is one of two counselors from New Jersey to win this very prestigious award.

"The Yale Educator Recognition Program recognizes outstanding educators from around the world who support and inspire their students to perform at high levels and to achieve excellence. Of this year’s 317 nominees, who represent 41 US states and 19 countries, 57 teachers and 24 counselors were selected to receive the award. Matriculating students are invited to nominate high school educators, and a committee of Yale admissions officers reviews each nomination individually and designates recipients."

post_text: For June’s We Rock Spotlight we would like to celebrate all of our incredible students, parents, and staff. We know this was not the end of the year that anyone anticipated or hoped for. It has been difficult and trying but we have shown resilience and come together as a community! From our food service workers continuing to provide food to our students every week, to our teachers who had to reassess their lesson plans and find new ways to stay engaged with students, to the incredible OCSD parents who have done an amazing job transitioning into remote in-home learning, to our awesome students who have continued to work hard and show us their Red Raider spirit! We thank and commend everyone in the OCSD community for coming together to help each other! Our Ocean City School community ROCKS!!!
text: For June’s We Rock Spotlight we would like to celebrate all of our incredible students, parents, and staff. We know this was not the end of the year that anyone anticipated or hoped for. It has been difficult and trying but we have shown resilience and come together as a community! From our food service workers continuing to provide food to our students every week, to our teachers who had to reassess their lesson plans and find new ways to stay engaged with students, to the incredible OCSD parents who have done an amazing job transitioning into remote in-home learning, to our awesome students who have continued to work hard and show us their Red Raider spirit! We thank and commend everyone in the OCSD community for coming together to help each other! Our Ocean City School community ROCKS!!!

post_text: For May’s We Rock Spotlight we would like to celebrate our incredible Class of 2020. Our seniors have worked so hard not only over the last four years, but throughout the last 12 years. From kindergarteners beginning to navigate their surroundings to soon-to-be high school graduates getting ready to take the plunge into the big wide world, the Ocean City Class of 2020 has flourished before our eyes! Our seniors rock for their academic achievements, their record-breaking athleticism, their passion for clubs and extracurriculars, their involvement in their community, and their strong spirits. We are lucky to have such incredible students in our district and in our community! The Ocean City Class of 2020 ROCKS!!

post_text:
Information Regarding the US 2020 Census:

The U.S. Census Bureau last week mailed requests to complete the 2020 questionnaire. Please take the time to do this as soon as possible. A complete count is vital in determining funding and services for all members of our community. At this time, residents can respond online at 2020census.gov or by phone at 844-330-2020.

The questionnaire will ask for the 12-digit census ID that was mailed to your Ocean City home. If you are spending the winter in a different location but live in Ocean City for the majority of the year, please use the Census ID from your Ocean City address or follow the prompt “If you do not have a census ID, click here.” It’s important that you be counted in Ocean City.
text:
Information Regarding the US 2020 Census:

The U.S. Census Bureau last week mailed requests to complete the 2020 questionnaire. Please take the time to do this as soon as possible. A complete count is vital in determining funding and services for all members of our community. At this time, residents can respond online at 2020census.gov or by phone at 844-330-2020.

The questionnaire will ask for the 12-digit census ID that was mailed to your Ocean City home. If you are spending the winter in a different location but live in Ocean City for the majority of the year, please use the Census ID from your Ocean City address or follow the prompt “If you do not have a census ID, click here.” It’s important that you be counted in Ocean City.

3-16-20 Statement from Governor Murphy - Governor Murphy issued on March 16, 2020 Executive Order No. 104 that “All public, private, and parochial preschool program premises, and elementary and secondary schools, including charter and renaissance schools, shall be closed to students beginning Wednesday, March 18, 2020, and shall remain closed as long as this Order remains in effect.” Therefore, the Ocean City School District is closed until further notice. Additional school updates will be provided as they become available.

Stay up to date on COVID-19 and OCSD related information on our website

post_text:
For our March “We Rock” Spotlight, we would like to focus on our Ocean City Special Education Parent Advisory Group! OCSEPAG’s mission includes advocating for the understanding of, respect for, and support of, all children with special needs in the community. The Special Education Parent Advisory Group serves children ages three to twenty-one. OCSEPAG is hosting 2 upcoming events a Family Support, Share, and Socialize Event on Thursday, March 12th and a Fitness Fun Day event Saturday, May 9th. Our community ROCKS!

If you are looking to get involved with the organization or have questions, contact SEPAG President Jodee Wagner at jodeewagz@comcast.net!

Parents/guardians who are looking for resources can find them on our website!
https://oceancityschools.org/curriculumspecialed
